  "text": "After 14 days of culturing, cell colonies developed and were picked up to be maintained on the human amniotic epithelial cell (hAEC) feeder layer [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] , with ES medium usually used to culture human embryonic stem cells (hESCs) and composed of basal medium: 20% KnockOut Serum Replacement (Gibco), 1 mM L-glutamine (PAA, Cölbe, Germany), 1% nonessential amino acids (PAA, Cölbe, Germany), 0.1 mM 2-mercaptoethanol (Invitrogen), 13 mM HEPES, and 8 ng/ml human basic fibroblast growth factor (Invitrogen).",
